# Directory And Storage Policy

This file summarizes the {{PROJECT_NAME}} directories and the storage policy. Path variable values are mastered in `docs/entrypoint.md` section 0.

## 1. Storage Policy

| Location | Nature | Use |
|---|---|---|
| `{{PROJECT_VAR_BRACE}}` | local master<!-- if:SRC_MIRROR_ENABLED=yes -->, not a git repo<!-- endif --> | real data, source, results, runners |
| `{{REPO_VAR_BRACE}}` | git repo | common docs<!-- if:SRC_MIRROR_ENABLED=yes --> and the `src/` mirror<!-- endif --> |
| `${CLAUDE_DIR}` | task artifacts | Claude Code outputs and workspaces |
<!-- if:COMPUTE_ENV=colab -->| `${COMPUTE_DRIVE_VAR}` | transient compute workspace | experiment execution |<!-- endif -->

<!-- if:COMPUTE_ENV=colab -->
The transient compute drive may not retain past {{EXPERIMENT_UNIT_LABEL}} results. Cross-{{EXPERIMENT_UNIT_LABEL}} aggregation should happen in the local master, not on the transient drive.
<!-- endif -->

## 2. Workspace Tree

Representative structure of the local master:

```text
{{PROJECT_VAR_BRACE}}/
  src/
  datasets/
  results/
    {{EXPERIMENT_UNIT_LABEL}}-001/
    {{EXPERIMENT_UNIT_LABEL}}-002/
  runners/
  claude/
```

<!-- if:SRC_MIRROR_ENABLED=yes -->
The git docs repo at `{{REPO_VAR_BRACE}}` also holds a `src/` mirror of `{{PROJECT_VAR_BRACE}}/src/`. Edit the master copy under `{{PROJECT_VAR_BRACE}}/src/`; never edit the mirror directly.
<!-- endif -->

<!-- if:SRC_MIRROR_ENABLED=yes -->`{{PROJECT_VAR_BRACE}}` is not a git repo. Do not commit or push there.<!-- endif -->

## 3. Task Artifact Layout

Claude Code writes per-task artifacts under `${CLAUDE_DIR}`:

```text
${CLAUDE_DIR}/{TASK_ID}/
  outputs/
  workspace/
```

`outputs/` holds deliverables; `workspace/` holds copies and probes. Existing project files stay read-only; mutations happen inside the task directory.

## 4. TASK_ID Rule

`TASK_ID` format is `YYYYMMDD-HHMM-XXXX`, for example `20260529-0754-ANALYZE-result-sweep`.

- The `YYYYMMDD-HHMM` segment must be the real `date` value taken by the Claude Code run that generates the prompt or the runner, not a placeholder.
- The {{ROLE_TERM}} drafting a prompt chooses only the `LABEL-suffix` portion (such as `ANALYZE-result-sweep` or `IMPL-loss-patch`); the timestamp is owned by the executor and resolved with `date` at generation time.
- Do not insert an `XXXX` placeholder, a template tag, or a runtime `now()` expression in place of the timestamp; that loses the audit chain between the task report, the task directory, and the produced artifacts.
